Ospf 
====
open shortest path firat protocol
its a dynamic routing protocol that helps find the best path for data exchange in an IP network. 
It uses a link-state approach to create a map of the network topology and update Link-State tables as needed. 
OSPF is scalable, can adapt to network changes quickly, and provides efficient routing with minimal overhead

Read OSPF from linked in Cheat Sheet 

